text: Kristin Sroka (May 23, 1977, Leipzig) is a German rhythmic gymnast. Sroka competed for Germany in the rhythmic gymnastics individual all-around competition at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. There she was 14th in the qualification and advanced to the semifinal, in the semifinal she was 16th and didn't advance to the final of 10 competitors. == References == == External links == * * Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:German rhythmic gymnasts Category:Gymnasts at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gymnasts of Germany Category:Sportspeople from Leipzig
